{ I first played Armann, a 1200 player, until GM Aman Hambleton took over for the last 30 seconds. }
1. c4 Nf6 2. Nc3 e6 3. g3 c5 4. Bg2 Nc6 5. Nf3 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. d4 Be6 8. O-O Be7 9. Re1 O-O 10. Bg5 cxd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 h6 13. Bf4 Qb6 14. Qxb6 axb6 15. Red1 Rfd8 16. a3 Bd6 17. Nxd5 (17. Bxd6 Rxd6 18. Nb5 Rd7 { This is the line I expected him to play, not realizing he can directly take on d5. }) 17... Bxd5 18. Bxd5 (18. Bxd6 Rxd6 19. e4 Nxe4 20. Bxe4 Rad8 { Keeps the advantage for white. }) 18... Bxf4 19. Bxb7 Rxd1+ 20. Rxd1 Rb8 21. Bf3 Be5 22. b4 b5 23. Rc1 Bb2 24. Rb1 Bxa3 25. Rb3 Bc1 26. Kg2 Bg5 27. e3 (27. h4 Bd2 28. Rb2 (28. Rd3) 28... Bc3) 27... Nd7 28. h4 Be7 29. Bc6 Nf6 30. e4 { Around here, GM Aman Hambleton took over, and he went into pure flagging mode. } 30... Rb6 31. Ba8 Re6 32. f3 Ra6 33. Bb7 Ra2+ 34. Kh3 Ne8 35. e5 Nc7 36. Rc3 Ne6 37. Rc8+ Kh7 38. Be4+ g6 39. Re8 Bxb4 40. Bd5 Re2 41. Bxe6 fxe6 42. Rxe6 Kg7 43. Rb6 Rxe5 44. Rb7+ Kf6 45. f4 Re7 46. Rb6+ Kf7 47. Rxb5 Bc3 48. h5 Bg7 49. hxg6+ Kxg6 50. Kg4 Kh7 51. Rb6 Rf7 52. Rb5 Re7 53. Rh5 Rd7 54. Rh3 Rc7 55. Rh4 Rc3 56. Rh5 Bf6 57. Rf5 Kg6 58. Rd5 Rc6 59. Rh5 Re6 60. Rh3 Re3 61. f5+ Kg7 62. Kf4 Re7 63. Kg4 Rc7 64. Kf3 Rc4 { 0-1 Black wins. } 0-1


