1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. f3 Nc6 6. c4 e6 7. Nc3 Be7 8. Be3 O-O 9. Be2 (9. Qd2) 9... a6 10. Qd2 (10. O-O d5 11. cxd5 exd5 12. Nxc6 bxc6 13. e5 Nd7 14. f4 { Best play if black tries to get in d5 one move later. }) 10... Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bd7 12. O-O Rc8 13. Rac1 Bc6 14. Rfd1 Qa5?? { After he played this move, I immediately got excited about Nd5. A few seconds later (due to stream delay) I heard that he was upset with how big a blunder his move was, but was trying to hold it back in case I was listening. } 15. Nd5! Qd8 (15... Qxd2?? 16. Nxe7+ Kh8 17. Rxd2 $18) 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7 17. Bb6! { Stops a rook from defending d6, so my pressure on the d file is felt. } 17... Ne8 18. Kh1 f5!? { Black needs to get counterplay somehow. Even if it means opening up his king, it's important to activate the f rook and queen. } 19. exf5 Rxf5 20. Rc3 Rh5 21. Bf2 { [%csl Gh4] } (21. Kg1 Qh4 22. h3 { Scary. But with my e2 bishop holding everything, my dark squared bishop can quickly return to cover the newly weakened dark squares. }) 21... Qf6 { Here, white needs to do something quick or else the bishop, queen, and rook will become too much of a nuisance. } 22. Re3?! { Doesn't immediately address the mounting pressure, and allows d5 to be played. } 22... d5! 23. b3 { [%cal Gd5c4,Ge2c4] } 23... Qh6 { [%cal Gf2g3,Gf2g1] } (23... dxc4? 24. Bxc4) 24. Bg1? (24. Bg3 { Better shuts down the pressure mounting against my king. In reality, I was down to 20 seconds and couldn't calculate anything anymore. I simply wanted to keep my bishop defended (the h pawn is pinned), so opted for Bg1 instead. } 24... Nd6 { [%csl Gd6] } (24... Nf6 25. Rxe6)) 24... Nd6 25. c5?? (25. Bd3 { Necessary to stop the knight from entering f5 with great effect. }) 25... Nf5 { With the mate threat on g3, it's now completely over. } { [%csl Gg3][%cal Gf5g3] } 26. g4 Nxe3 27. Bxe3?? { With seconds left, I forgot about the pressure on h2. I figured this would win back a little material, at the expense of a slightly weakened king. } (27. gxh5 Nxd1 28. Qxh6 gxh6 29. Bxd1 { The only way to prolong the game, but it's completely over. }) 27... Rxh2+ { Whoops. } 28. Kg1 Rh1+ 29. Kf2 Qh2# { 0-1 Black wins by checkmate. } 0-1


