1. c4 Nf6 2. g3 g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nc3 O-O 5. e4 d6 6. Nge2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d3 Nh5 { [%cal Gf7f5] } 9. Nd5 f5 10. exf5 gxf5 11. f4 { [%clk 0:03:13] } 11... Nf6 { The end of any preparation I know. I know the engine likes white, but there are a few opportunities to attack on the open g file, so I enjoy these positions from both sides. } { [%clk 0:02:51] } 12. Rb1 { [%cal Gb2b4] } 12... a5 13. b3 Nb4 { [%cal Gb4a2,Gb4d5,Gc7c6] [%clk 0:02:38] } 14. Nec3 (14. Nxb4 axb4 { Black has the open a file and all the chances to win. }) 14... c6 { [%clk 0:02:34] } (14... Nfxd5 15. Nxd5 c6 { A better version of the game - the rook is not better placed on f6 than f8. }) 15. Nxf6+ Rxf6 16. fxe5? dxe5 { It didn't look like a mistake, but taking on e5 opens up my queen, and creates several threats against white's king. } { [%clk 0:02:31] } 17. Kh1 (17. a3 Qd4+ 18. Kh1 Nxd3 $17 { [%csl Gc3] }) 17... Qxd3 { [%clk 0:02:19] } 18. Qxd3 (18. Qh5 { [%cal Gh5e8] } 18... Qxc3 { White can't keep the queens on the board here. } 19. Qe8+ Rf8) 18... Nxd3 19. Bg5 Rf8 20. Na4 { My knight on d3 dominates his knight on a4. } { [%cal Ga4c5,Ga4b6,Gd3c5] } 20... h6 21. Be3 Be6 { [%cal Ga4c5,Gd3c5] } 22. Rbd1 (22. Nb6 Rad8 { Now black has perfect coordination. }) 22... e4 { [%clk 0:01:53] } 23. Nc5 Nxc5 24. Bxc5 Rfd8 25. Rxd8+ Rxd8 26. Bb6 Rd2! { Activating the rook is more important that getting behind the a pawn. } 27. Bxa5 (27. Rf2 Rxf2 28. Bxf2 a4 $17 { Pressure on c4 and the passed e4 pawn - black is doing great. } { [%cal Ge6c4] } 29. g4 fxg4 30. Bxe4) 27... Rxa2 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Gg2h3] } 28. Bb6 Rb2 29. c5?? { Trapping his bishop on b6. Immediately, Eric said "strategically that was a blunder by me" } (29. Bh3? Rxb3! 30. Ba7!? (30. Bxf5? Bxf5 31. Rxf5 Rxb6 $19) 30... Bxc4 31. Rxf5 e3 $19) (29. Bc5!? Rxb3 30. Rc1 $17) 29... Rxb3 30. Bh3 Kh7 31. Bxf5+ Bxf5 32. Rxf5 e3 33. Rf1 e2 { [%clk 0:01:22] } 34. Re1 { [%csl Gb2] [%clk 0:02:37] } 34... Re3?! (34... Rb2 35. Kg2 (35. Ba5 Bd4 36. Kg2 Bxc5 37. Kf3 b6!! { [%csl Gd2,Gc3][%cal Gb2b3] } 38. Bc3 Rb3 $19 39. Rc1 Rxc3+ 40. Rxc3 e1=Q) 35... Bc3 { A much cleaner version than in the game. }) 35. Kg2 Bc3 36. Kf2! { I missed that this move would counterattack my own rook. Thankfully, I still have a stunning finish. } 36... Bxe1+ 37. Kxe3 Bxg3!! { The bishop cannot be taken or the pawn promotes. } 38. Kxe2 Bxh2 39. Kf3 { 0-1 Black wins. } { Amazingly, I actually had just over a minute here. I could easily win this endgame. } { [%cal Gh7g6,Gg6f5,Gf5g4,Gh6h5,Gh5h4,Gh4h3,Gh3h2,Gh2h1] [%clk 0:02:41] } 0-1


